ticle needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed february  learn how and when to remove this template message volaris iata icao callsign y voi volaris founded   years ago  commenced operations   years ago  hubs guadalajara international airport mexico city international airport tijuana international airport focus cities cancún international airport los angeles international airport monterrey international airport frequentflyer program vclub subsidiaries volaris costa rica fleet size  destinations  company slogan precios que te hacen viajar spanish get out of town prices english parent company vuela compañia de aviación headquarters mexico city mexico key people enrique beltranena ceo fernando suarez cfo holger blankenstein cco website volariscom volaris legally concesionaria vuela compañía de aviación sab de cv bmv volara nyse vlrs is a mexican lowcost airline based in santa fe álvaro obregón mexico city with its hub in guadalajara mexico city and tijuana and as well focus cities in cancun los angeles and monterrey it is the countrys second largest airline after aeroméxico and serves domestic and international destinations within the americas it is a leading competitor in the mexican domestic airline market now with a market share of over  of domestic traffic contents  history  international operations  corporate affairs  destinations  codeshare agreements  fleet  trivia  references  external links historyedit the preoperations phase founding of the legal entities and setting up of the required infrastructure started in august  under the name vuela airlines major initial shareholders of the company were grupo televisa the worlds biggest spanishlanguage media conglomerate inbursa an insurance company owned by billionaire carlos slim avianca then taca airlines and the discovery americas fund each of these partners invested  of the initial cost of activities or  million usd on july  it was announced that televisa and inbursa had sold their stake in volaris leaving the ownership of volaris as follows avianca then taca airlines with roberto and maria cristina kriete  investment fund discovery americas over  and indigo partners fund led by former america west ceo b franke ticket sales started on january   and following the delivery of the airlines first aircraft the first noncommercial flight was operated in february  scheduled revenue flights were launched on march   with the inaugural flight having been operated from toluca to tijuana initially the airline avoided flying to mexico city because of it being a congested and expensive airport the airline took over several slots that had been owned by nowdefunct mexicana and its subsidiaries mexicanaclick and mexicanalink establishing service in september  in march  it announced that its hub in toluca would move to guadalajara on june   the airline launched a frequent flyer program called vclub it is the membership program that provides special fares offers last minute travel deals and other perks customers can save up to  using the vclub membership on june   paypal became a payment alternative for the airline enabling customers to purchase tickets directly from the airlines website on september   volaris announced a codeshare partnership with a german airline condor passengers of condor are able to fly to more international destinations on march   the airline celebrated its seventh anniversary offering passengers  off all flights it has done this every year since then volaris announced the creation of a subsidiary volaris costa rica in march  the subsidiary based at juan santamaría international airport in costa rican capital san josé started operations in november  international operationsedit in november  volaris announced a codeshare agreement with usbased lowcost carrier southwest airlines in april  volaris announced the start of usbound flights out of toluca and guadalajara initially to los angeles and oakland to feed into the hubs of southwest airlines later on usflights were also offered from zacatecas and morelia with monterreylos angeles and fresno in planning on december   volaris started services between chicagomidway and guadalajara it is volaris fourth international destination first international service to a secondary airport and the longest route of volaris history after mexicana de aviacións shutdown volaris took over many of mexicanas international destinations and flights from its focus city guadalajara on february   it was announced that volaris would acquire mexicanas destination fresno and would begin service on april   fresno was volaris first us destination where it did not partner with southwest airlines the airline began using guadalajara international airport as an american gateway hub in late  volaris sought permission to fly between dallasfort worth and mexico city along with a number of other usmexico routes volaris submitted the request on february   and the us department of transportation granted approval on february  however volaris did not launch the service until over four years later on april   when it began flights between dallasfort worth and guadalajara volaris received approval to fly to southern californias san diego international airport on july   volaris then began nonstop flights between orlando and guadalajara from july   volaris started service between sacramento and guadalajara on november   volaris then began flights between denver and mexico city on december   on february   volaris and southwest stopped codesharing southwest decided to focus more on the mexican market with airtran airways instead of codesharing with volaris volaris began flights between phoenix and guadalajara on october   volaris began flying to its first destination in texas at the time to san antonio from guadalajara on december   volaris began nonstop flights between chicagoohare and mexico city on december   this replaced volaris chicagomidwaymexico city flights volaris then began flights between guadalajara and ontario california a reliever airport in the greater los angeles area on april   volaris applied to fly mexicanas former portland to guadalajara route the application was granted and service to portland began on october   volaris began its second destination in florida fort lauderdale–hollywood international airport from mexico city on december   and then also from guadalajara on december   the airline has ceased flying to fort lauderdale and replaced the route with nonstop flights to miami from mexico city and guadalajara volaris began nonstop flights between reno–tahoe international airport and guadalajara on december   volaris planned to launch service to william p hobby airport in houston texas as soon as the new terminal was completed but the airline chose to begin flying to houstonintercontinental from guadalajara on march   instead volaris began its first nonstop flights to the northeastern united states when it began service between new yorkjfk and guadalajara on july   and on march   started nonstop service between mexico city and new yorkjfk in the summer of  volaris launched its first ever international flights outside the continental united states to guatemala on june  to san juan puerto rico on july  and to san josé costa rica on september  on july   volaris began service to seattle from guadalajara on may   the airline announced it will begin non stop flights between monterrey and dallasfort worth service began on july   volaris began the first service link between austin and guadalajara on august   volaris has confirmed it does not plan to fly to santiago de chile and rather focus in the us central america and domestic markets after a local newspaper announced the airline had plans to begin operations in south america on march  volaris began nonstop service between guadalajara and milwaukee on november   volairs will offer nonstop service between guadalajara and san bernardino corporate affairsedit the airline is headquartered in santa fe álvaro obregón mexico city it formerly had its headquarters on the first floor of prolongación paseo de la reforma  in peña blanca santa fe destinationsedit main article volaris destinations volaris operates scheduled flights to mexico  and elsewhere in the americas  from its hub in guadalajara international airport in guadalajara mexico city international airport in mexico city and tijuana international airport in tijuana and focus cities in cancun international airport in cancun los angeles international airport in los angeles and monterrey international airport in monterrey codeshare agreementsedit condor fleetedit volaris airbus a as of july  the volaris fleet consists of the following aircraft volaris fleet aircraft in service orders passengers economy notes airbus a  —  airbus a    airbus aneo    deliveries from  airbus a  —  total   triviaedit the former volaris safety video featured actress claudia lizaldi the current volaris safety video features young children demonstrating the safety procedures referencesedit  aeromexico trades domestic  international market share gains for lower yields as q profits drop retrieved  july    aeromexico and volaris increase international spread to strengthen yields and vivaaerobus follows retrieved  july    indigo partners buys stake in mexicos volaris flightglobalcom  retrieved    sala de prensa volarismx retrieved    media center volarismx retrieved    press release  condor and the mexican airline volaris enter into partnership pdf  september  retrieved  november    volaris  off airfare to mexicotoday only slickdeals retrieved  july    volaris sets up costa rican unit eyes h launch chaviation  march  retrieved  december    rodríguez raquel  march  los precios para volar entre centroamérica serán los más bajos the fares to fly in central america will be the lowest la república in spanish retrieved  december    volaris costa rica commences operations chaviation  december  retrieved  december    volaris get us approval for dfwmexico city flights airline biz blog retrieved  july    volaris wants to fly dfwguadalajara route too airline biz blog retrieved  july    volaris to start mexico city – orlando from july  retrieved  july     archived may   at the wayback machine  southwest and volaris to end partnership   flight global  retrieved    volaris to start guadalajara – san antonio service from middecember  retrieved  july    volaris to start mexico city – phoenix  chicago o’hare service from dec  retrieved  july    volaris to start guadalajara – ontario service from april  retrieved  july    volaris applies for pdxgdl service  flyertalk forums retrieved  july    volaris adds ft lauderdale operation from dec  retrieved  july    volaris adds guadalajara – reno service from middec  retrieved  july    houston airport operator envisions hobby offering international flights in  markets retrieved  july    volaris adds guadalajara – houston route from latemarch  retrieved  july    volaris now arriving in new york yahoo finance  march  retrieved  july    volaris makes first flights into central america financial news  financial news distribution  financial news pr archived from the original on  july  retrieved  july    volaris  volaris announces flights to puerto rico retrieved  july    volaris  may  volaris announces flights to costa rica retrieved  july    volaris adds new guadalajara – us routes in q routesonline retrieved  april    httpmmileniocomnegociosvolarislanzadirectadallastexashtml  httpenelairemxvolarisinauguralarutamonterreydallasfortworth  volaris adds new guadalajara – us routes in q routesonline retrieved  april    httpwwwdesdesclcomvolarisdescartaoperacionesenchileyhtml  httptravellatamcomnotaaerolineamexicanavolarispreparasuaterrizajeenchile  volaris opens  destinations in spanish compañía periodística meridiano march  retrieved april     information about volaris volaris retrieved 